            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STANDING_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Standing?",
          "next": "N_STANDING_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STANDING_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The notice includes a definition in the margin, like it\u2019s tired of being questioned. (pause) \u201cStanding: recognized eligibility to be processed.\u201d (pause) \u201cProcessed\u201d is underlined once. (pause) The underline is perfectly straight. It\u2019s its own kind of threat.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Service class?",
          "next": "N_SERVICE_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Another margin block, pre-emptive. (pause)\n\n\u201cSERVICE CLASS: UNRESOLVED.\u201d (pause)\n\u201cIncorrect service class assignments may affect standing.\u201d (pause)\n\nThe sentence is written like an apology that learned to protect itself.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHOW_REF_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "MTA_NOTICE_REF.",
          "next": "N_SHOW_REF_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHOW_REF_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Saying it out loud makes it real, less defensible. Reference string looks like external docket. (pause) Prefix plus jurisdiction stub. A queue-like tail implies you\u2019re not first.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERPRET_REF_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It reads like external docketing: jurisdiction stub; processing lane code; queue-position tail. (pause) It\u2019s designed to be cited, not understood.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERPRET_REF_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You can\u2019t place it confidently. It\u2019s too-clean, too-standardized\u2014like it expects your systems already agree with it.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_BARCODE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "High-contrast. Machine-friendly. No smearing. No aging. Formatted as if every reader already agrees on meaning.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_RECORDS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The records door has three locks and a posted schedule. (pause)\nThe schedule is handwritten, then photocopied until it becomes law. (pause)\n\nSomeone has added: \u201cNO TUBE DROPS INSIDE RECORDS.\u201d (pause)\nUnder that: \u201cException: Compliance.\u201d",
          "next": "N_RECORDS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RECORDS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_FAX",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A placard above the wall fax lists numbers by jurisdiction, as if geography still solves things. (pause) There\u2019s a blank line labeled \u201cNON-LOCAL / OTHER.\u201d (pause) The blank line has been used often enough to be glossy.",
          "next": "N_FAX_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAX_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_ASK_MTA_FAX",
              "text": "ask: \u201cMTA have a fax?\u201d",
              "next": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "MTA have a fax?",
          "next": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The placard doesn\u2019t answer. (pause) It offers a procedure instead. (pause)\n\n\u201cIf the destination is unlisted: (pause) transmit to ADMIN SERVICES. (pause) NOTE \u2018NON-LOCAL\u2019 IN THE COVER SHEET.\u201d (pause)\n\nThe instruction feels like it was written after someone tried to be clever.",
          "next": "R_TO_FAX_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_FIRE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The fire panel has a taped note in block letters: \u201cDO NOT SILENCE WITHOUT INCIDENT NUMBER.\u201d (pause)\nBeneath it, smaller: \u201cEven if it\u2019s annoying.\u201d (pause)\nThe building\u2019s priorities are clear.",
          "next": "N_FIRE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FIRE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Who sent this?",
          "next": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The printout answers like authority: it names a category, not a person. (pause)\n\n\u201cMANAGING AUTHORITY: METASTABLE TRANSFER AUTHORITY (MTA).\u201d (pause)\n\nNo signature. No phone tree. Just an acronym. It expects compliance as its own contact.",
          "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lift the page from the tray. (pause) The paper resists, then releases. (pause) Like it wants to be on record. (pause)\n\nThe tube station light stays lit. (pause) It doesn\u2019t thank you. (pause) It just waits for the next step you didn\u2019t agree to.",
          "next": "N_TAKE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TAKE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_TAKE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TAKE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the hallway.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You treat it as evidence, not mail. (pause)\nYou keep the original. You note the header. You keep the barcodes intact. (pause)\nYou do not summarize from memory.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_POST_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_POST_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA",
              "text": "use: Add OLEA signatory initials in the margin.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.oleaAuthorizedSignatory",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA_LINE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_INITIAL_CHECK",
              "text": "use: Add chain-of-custody initials anyway (boring, defensible).",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.oleaAuthorizedSignatory",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "bureaucracy",
                  "dc": 10
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL",
              "text": "use: No annotation. Keep it clean.",
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL_LINE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add small, boring OLEA signatory initials in the margin.\nChain of custody is dull handwriting.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add initials and a timestamp in the margin\u2014nothing authoritative, just consistent. (pause)\nIt reads like a person who expects to be questioned and intends to survive it.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You start to write, then stop.\nWithout standing to claim, handwriting can be argued about later.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You don\u2019t initial it. You still handle it like it will be read aloud later. (pause) By someone paid to misunderstand you.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The reference number\u2014MTA_NOTICE_REF\u2014becomes something you can cite. (pause) Without sounding like you made it up.\n\nThe tube station indicator finally clicks off. (pause) Not resolved. Just recorded.",
          "next": "END_RECEIVE_MTA_NOTICE"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_RECEIVE_MTA_NOTICE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "receive_mta_notice",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
